<a href="http://www.methart.com"><img src="http://www.methart.com/button/methart-fire2.jpg" border="0"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ulinabo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LinaBo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>PK Angel</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/27/01 12:19:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.linabo.50megs.com/linapic.jpg width=100 height=78></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: got some oil pastels. now what?</span><hr size=1> oh, yes, i know what you're talking about. those blending sticks that look like compacted paper? they have them here, they're cheap, I'll go get one today. <p>Disclaimer: All opinions voiced by Lina may potentially be only so-much-B.S.
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ucaptainmeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Captain Meth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/27/01 12:39:32 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.methart.com/t_meth2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: got some oil pastels. now what?</span><hr size=1> Yeah, those are the things.  You can sharpen them too if they start to get a little dull, or if thaty start to pick up too many dark colours.  As well, you can go the welfare way like me and just use the stick from a lollipop.  Uh, but cut off the end that you chewed on.  Then just sharpen that as well. <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
