<a href="http://www.methart.com"><img src="http://www.methart.com/button/methart-fire2.jpg" border="0"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ulinabo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LinaBo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>PK Angel</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/27/01 2:50:51 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.linabo.50megs.com/linapic.jpg width=100 height=78></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: got some oil pastels. now what?</span><hr size=1> I got a thin one and a fat one from the art supply place. cost $2.78 altogether, not much<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Disclaimer: All opinions voiced by Lina may potentially be only so-much-B.S.
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uazoth30k.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azoth30k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/27/01 3:05:34 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.com/assassinsguild/azhead.jpg Height=86 Width=70></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: got some oil pastels. now what?</span><hr size=1> If you got actual oil pastels you can also use a small amount of paint thinner to get them to blend smoothly(we're talking a couple of drops here). I also think that they might actually sell a special thinner just for pastels. Coloured paper can apparently produce some neat effects. Other than that the only suggestions I got from my drawing professors on pastel drawing was to treat it more like paint than pencils... <p><br>Cannot forget. Cannot remember.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukennygeeze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kenny Geeze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/27/01 6:58:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.lespaul.com/menu1/deluxe.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: got some oil pastels. now what?</span><hr size=1> If you decide to put the pastel down thick on the paper and burnish with a lighter color, you can rub it with the back of a spoon for some interesting effects. Experiment with that.<br>
Pastels work well on black construction paper. At least I think they do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showMessage?topicID=2421.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showMessage?topicID=2419.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=2413.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.threadControl?topicID=2413.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2413.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2413.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="polykarbonbbsfrm18">PK-BBS Rules and Regulations!<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm3">News and Updates<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm2">Photoshop and Art questions<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm4">General Manga/Anime Discussion<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm5">Japanese Language Help<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm23">art in progress<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm13">Black and White Art<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm14">Color Art